The paper deals with supervised binary hashing for image retrieval, which is a problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses optimization techniques for learning hash functions, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG). The use of affinity-based loss functions and auxiliary coordinates suggests that the paper may also be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper's focus on image retrieval and optimization techniques may also make it relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL), as text-based image retrieval is a common application.
